reviews: This hotel is located directly across the street from the St. Placide Metro station, and is within walking distance of many nice places to eat and drink. The surrounding area was quite active with outdoor seating, including after dark, and we felt very safe walking around late at night. The front desk staff was friendly and helpful with answering questions.The room itself is small by US standards, but is typical for an older European hotel. Our room got a good cleaning daily, and even had a small balcony with a table and 2 chairs. There was a fairly large flat-screen TV that we never used. Would definitely considered staying here again, if I ever get an opportunity to return to Paris.

This hotel provided us with a good base in Paris. Our room (22) was quite small but it was fine for a couple of nights. The bed was comfortable. Some reviews mention the traffic noise. The windows were good enough that it didn't disturb our sleep even though we faced on to the main street. Might be an issue in the summer if you want a window open. The room was spotless as was the bathroom. There was a fridge and a kettle. The safe was too small to put a small iPad in. The complimentary teabags etc. were a bit skimpy but reception was happy to top up. The staff in general were very friendly and helpful. Teaspoons instead of wooden stirring sticks would have been preferable.
We opted to have the buffet breakfast in the hotel which we feel was reasonable at €16 pp. There was a good selection to choose from including ham, pastries, croissants, bread stick, jams, yogurts, cereal, fresh fruit salad and pre-packed cheese. There was a member of staff who prepared fresh orange juice and pots of tea for us but we were not offered a tea refill before she disappeared. Boiled eggs were cold and in the fridge. Some wholemeal bread with a softer crust would have been good.
Apart from the room being small, in the bathroom access to the WC between the shower screen and the sink might be a bit of a squeeze for some, despite the bathroom being generally spacious. The trimmings seem to have been cut back with no wardrobe or drawers, just hanging space, "catch all" shampoo/shower gel in the shower, same at the sink.
We felt the price of the room was rather high for what we got at €241 per night, but we like Best Western hotels. The location is good with two different metro stations/lines nearby that gave you access to the city.
Apart from the price we would be perfectly happy to return to this hotel.

Pros: Location is good, a great place to start walking, and close to several Metro lines. Room had a hot-pot and a refrigerator (no freezer compartment). Staff is helpful and cheerful; they all speak good English. Breakfast is only cold stuff, plus tea and coffee. It's a good assortment of cereal, pancakes, yogurt, ham, breads, jelly & honey, hard-boiled eggs, etc. It's buffet, serve yourself, as much as you like. Don't prepay for every day; you can go when you like, and they charge you at the end. If you want only coffee/tea, it's 6 Euros. Otherwise, 16 Euros.

Disliked · I had Room 10, on the 2nd floor, facing the street. The room is small for one person, 9' x 13' plus bathroom. But it's a double, with 2 single beds. And the street-side is very noisy: police cars day and night, motorcycles, lots of traffic. The windows overlook an outside cafe right below, which is very noisy in the evening. Minor quibble: there's no washcloth, just the towels. I stayed 8 nights, paid an average of 200 Euros/nt. Plus breakfasts. It seems like a lot of money for a small noisy room, but I guess it's probably a pretty good deal, compared to other places. I guess.

Victor, WIlliam and Slyvia will take great care of you !
They made going to certain tourist spots easy - and were able to book us cars whenever we needed it. Answer any an all questions even if they were simple / silly

Was clean & comfortable. It is older so look elsewhere if you want something more modern. The staff were friendly. Steps from the metro. The only downside is there was a massive gap under the door which let in light from the hallway. The bathtub was nice & deep but the depth with the movable plastic flexi shower wall made it harder to get in & out of.

In a word, Excellent. Excellent experience. Excellent service. Excellent value for money. We very much enjoyed coming back to this hotel. We first stayed here 30 years ago when we first married and visited Paris while we were living in the South of France (we also stayed at the BW Hotel de Cluny, but that is no longer a BW property I believe). Although thing has been updated, the charm of the place was still present. Highly recommend this hotel.

The location of the hotel was perfect for walking to most of the sites in Paris. It’s very close to two metro stations and bus stops, so it is easy to travel everywhere. The room was very small which is to be expected in Paris. It was clean and quiet.
We weren’t told, but coffee from the main floor cafe is included. We discovered this upon check out when we weren’t charged.

The hotel is across the street from Saint-Placide metro, which was incredibly convenient for traveling to other parts of Paris. The only problems I bumped into during my stay was with the air conditioning. I know that when travelling to Europe there oftentimes may not be air conditioning. I have no problem with this. However, I chose this hotel partially because it advertised air conditioning and I knew the weather was going to be pretty hot. The first night my room's air conditioning was not working. I asked the front desk if they could help. They ended up moving me to a different room, but the AC also did not work there. Rip. I asked for a fan. The front desk gentleman informed me that he had distributed the last fan just a few hours previously. So invest in more portable fans! Other than this mishap, this hotel is a great option for travelling on a budget, especially for solo travelers. The room was somewhat small. This was fine for me, as I was travelling alone. The bathroom was very nice and not cramped like others I had experienced. There is a little cafe and Asian restaurant across the street from the hotel that I frequented most days! I believe they were called Thevenin and Nezard. Additionally, I felt pretty safe staying here as your room key opens the otherwise locked front door at night.

Amazing location for getting out and about in Paris. We were very warmly greeted and given our room key. The room was tiny but had everything in it so not an issue and it was a central hotel. Bathroom was OK but the shower was a little piddly. The bed was very comfy.
Downside was the Aircon which we couldn't really get working properly although it did cool the room for a bit and the telly wasn't able to show the UK channels that were advertised and front desk did say they were aware and had called a technician.
Otherwise a great hotel in a great location. We didn't eat or drink so can't comment on that. Nice big mirror in reception 😆

Great value for money and friendly staff. My room unfortunately faced a wall and so was dark which made it seemed even smaller. I am not complaining as the room was only for sleeping but did mean I gave it a lower rating than the other categories

The location was ideal....we walked to almost all of our destinations. I enjoyed the charm of the hotel and I felt it provided everything we needed. It felt very French...The staff were so friendly and acco

Hotel is across the street from Saint-Placide metro which is great for travelers heading to/from Paris Est (long distance TGV / ICE trains), since you don't have to transfer as they're both on Metro line 4.

The hotel bathroom appears newly renovated, however the bathtub is oddly angled with no safety bars - not great for elderly guests. Also avoid rooms on the 6th floor as the elevator only goes up to floor 5 and you have to use the stairs. The wood floors are very creaky overall - could hear noises from adjacent rooms.

Great front desk staff - always friendly and helpful.

My daughter and I stayed for 5 nights and we enjoyed the friendly staff, convenient location, great neighborhood. Our first night was in a smaller dark room on the 1st floor and there was construction noise right next to our room early in the morning. The staff was extremely accommodating and moved us to a different room on a higher floor with the street view, which was bright and comfortable and away from the construction noise. We greatly appreciated their friendly and accommodating staff. The location was very convenient.

Good location, close to old town and train station. Efficient and friendly front desk, and adequate gym. The locks on bathroom doors were broken and there is a bit of noise from the street at night , but not too disturbing.

This hotel was great, it was very good value for money, the staff were very friendly, and the rooms were very clean. There were also 2 train stations on 2 different train lines very right near the hotel which was helpful.

Excellent location, close to a Metro station which means major sites are easily accessible. Lots of choices for places to eat. Excellent boulangerie/patisserie close by. Helpful and friendly staff. Overall, we had very good experience here.

we enjoyed the Aramis St. Germain - my only suggestion would be for a handle to hold onto getting in and out of the bath tub. It was higher than the floor so was difficult to step out of the tub, and could be dangerous if one slipped.

I read many reviews before selecting this property near Luxembourg Saint Germain. Far exceeded my expectations of modern cleanliness. Rooms are efficient and the elevator is small, but these are insignificant details. Kind and proactive staff, comfortable bed, nice bathroom. A minor issue with the air conditioning unit was resolved BEFORE I inquired about it. What a delight! I would absolutely stay here again. Thank you, BW Aramis Saint Germaine! Wonderful walking neighborhood and experience.

Great place to stay and we would stay here again! Large room and great price for Paris. Extremely friendly staff. Very close to Montparnasse train station and several metro stops, Bakeries and restaurants everywhere!

It is in front of the Saint-Placid metro station. It is surrounded by restaurants, bars, little super markets, stores, etc. 5 minutes away walk to Luxembourg Gardens. All staff is very friendly. The cleaning service is great. The only problem we had the first day was that the A/C did not work in our room, and we were moved to a different one.

The ARAMIS Saint-Germain is my “go to” hotel in Paris. This was my fifth stay here. It is in a central location to walk and to take the metro to anywhere in Paris. The rooms are typically on the small side, but they have comfortable beds and are quiet for a very good night’s sleep. And the rooms feature a very nice Nespresso machine. All you need for a night or several nights in Paris. The best thing about the ARAMIS is the first-rate staff in the hotel. They are the most helpful reception staff anywhere. They will help you with anything you need or might want. I cannot praise them enough. In the area you will find whatever you need - very good bakeries, cafes, the wonderful Bon Marche store and the Jardin du Luxembourg. This hotel is really the perfect Paris hotel. Thanks again to the excellent reception staff here.

The hotel staff was friendly and polite! The rooms are small but well maintained. Nothing fancy the furniture and things like lamps and desks are definitely on the cheap and used side. So I found the price of $746.00 for 3 nights double occupancy a bit on the expensive side for what your getting. It maybe just what one needs to expect from being in Paris these days? Don’t know but seems a bit pricey to me.

A lovely and welcoming hotel, very well located in Saint-Germain close to Montparnasse, right across the street from Saint-Placide Metro. Amazingly friendly staff who looked after us and our every need. We booked well in advance and were given a spacious and light-filled double room, on the fourth floor with large windows facing a quiet back street – at a very reasonable rate given the prime location and high standard. Impeccably clean room and facilities, good security, comfortable bed and pillows. Wifi worked fine with Teams meetings for a couple of hours work at the room desk. Breakfast at the hotel or take a pick from very good boulangeries and restaurants you can literally see from the hotel entrance. I can highly recommend Hotel Aramis (and Paris in April is probably as good as it gets when choosing a Euro city long weekend). À bientôt!

The hotel is situated right in the heart of the Montparnasse area with a lot of good authentic restaurants, boulangerie and pâtisseries nearby, some of which are Michelin starred but in a very reasonable price. The staff was exceptionally nice and helpful. They accommodate your needs to the best of their ability, in the quickest way possible. 10/10 would recommend

Polite and efficient service with a helpful night porter. Room and bathroom were fine. Woken up by loud banging next door - hotel did not warn us this would happen and we didn’t get an apology or a goodwill gesture of compensation which was disappointing. Good location, right near cafes and metro stations and the Luxembourg gardens.

Great location! Right by metro (across the street) and front desk can get you a cab in a matter of minutes. Opted for breakfast included - Just cold options which were the same everyday. Lots of shops and restaurants/cafes/bistros just outside the front door. Rooms are not large but manageable. Good shower water pressure. Front desk was friendly and helpful.

This is my third time staying here. The staff are lovely. The location is perfect. It’s clean and just perfect. The rooms are quiet and well designed. There is everything you need and more. I love it!

Loved the place , everything was perfect and just the way my son and I wanted things . Perfect place to go if you are looking for convenience , comfort and cleanliness all in one place . The hotel is surrounded by high street shops as well as 3 metro lines which is all within a 5 minute walk.

The hotel has normal sized bedroom for central Paris but with a rather spacious bathroom incl bathtub. Small safety box not fitting laptops or iPads, but the hotel reception could take our stuff in their bigger box. Short distance to metro stations Saint Placide (Nr 4) and Rennes (nr 12).

The location is suitable to travel within the city. Instead of taking cabs, from this location we could just walk around and visit the sites. The staff are really really helpful and supportive. Had a great stay. Will be back soon. :)

I had a small, comfortable room in this hotel - exactly what I required. Great location. The manager was professional, friendly and helpful. I would say that in terms of the room I booked, it would good value and a great choice for a weekend or a three night stay.

We enjoyed our visit for 3 nights. Location is excellent with metro stop just across the street, lots of stores, cafes etc. nearby, Very friendly and approachable staff. We stayed at the cheapest room option which while small was all that we really needed. While it's at a street crossing our room was very quiet with windows closed.

I had a horrible experience at this hotel.

First, at check-in, the agent didn't know how to apply my three gift cards and blamed me for not having emailed the gift cards to the hotel in advance. Secondly, he did not provide nor offer a welcome gift for me as a Diamond Select member, as required by the terms and conditions of Best Western. When I mentioned the welcome gift to him, he said he had never heard of Diamond Select, nor was he aware of the different status levels with Best Western. He obviously didn't recognize my status in any way. Third, he didn't provide the welcome drink that the hotel prominently advertises at the top of its webpage.

I emailed the hotel management and spoke to the manager in-person the next day, and he refused to offer anything for this terrible experience such as a complimentary breakfast. He insisted that his hotel didn't need to offer the Diamond Select welcome gift because his hotel had upgraded me. He failed to recognize that the welcome gift is separate from a potential upgrade, in direct violation of the terms and conditions. He also said that it was unreasonable for his staff to be familiar with Best Western Rewards, such as how to process gift cards or what status levels are. Finally, he said the welcome drink wasn't offered due to COVID, even though the webpage still prominently advertises this.

This hotel should lose its Best Western affiliation immediately because it has no respect for Best Western elite status.

I have nothing but good things to say about Aramis hotel on Rue de Rennes in the St. Germain area of Paris. Although it is part of the Best Western chain, it really feels like family. It is in a great location with lots of everything you need at your doorstep, including metro stops, and only a 10-minute walk from Jardin du Luxembourg. What sets this hotel apart is the excellent service. Although it is not family run, the front desk staff makes you feel like family from the minute you walk in until the minute you check out. Our appointment at a lab for our required Covid PCR test for return to the United States was a few hours after our check out time. The hotel was going to shut down for a month and they were getting ready to leave. But they kept our luggage and waited until we had the test done before closing the hotel. The three gentlemen running the front desk always went above and beyond with any questions or concerns we had. We had a very nice room on the fourth floor with plenty of counter space, refrigerator, and a real armoire. There was plenty of room for our suitcases.

The building is triangular facing two very busy streets—Rue de Rennes and Vaugirard—so there is a lot of noise if you open windows (unavoidable if you choose to stay in the city). However, the double paned windows work like magic and shut out the noise completely. We had the air on during the day but opened windows at night to get the cool breeze. It worked out.

The best part about this hotel is its location, double paned windows, and especially the service. We can’t praise them enough for treating everyone like family and genuinely caring to make sure all guests have a very pleasant stay. Aramis hotel is our home away from home in Paris.

Our trip to Paris was delayed by a year due to Covid. Our travel agent became a complete waste with rebooking our trip. We’ve stayed in Paris before, but the Aramis in St Germain has become our favorite place to stay. Staff and accommodations were excellent.

This Hotel is right where you want to be in the middle of Paris. Very cosy room. It had everything we wanted with a great staff to help. We found the bed to be very comfortable. I would recommend this hotel to anyone that doesn't mind a small room. We loved it.

I liked so much about the hotel...the staff were great, the location is fabulous, everything was great...except the mattress! We stayed for five nights and I don't think I slept well a single night. The mattress was very hard and I found the pillows uncomfortable as well. Unfortunately, it really doesn't matter about everything else that is good about the hotel if the beds are so uncomfortable. If they fixed this, it would really make this a great hotel.

This is a local area but not far from tourist attractions. It's maybe a 5 min metro ride to everywhere.
I would easily recommend this place and stay here once more.

The latin quarter is wonderful and the bars and everyone is great.

It will be very evident you are around locals especially at night. the bar next to this hotel is perfect. It is just as friendly and upbeat as staff here.

I had to find an option to host my extended family for a weekend.
I couldn’t hope for a better alternative at this price.
This hotel is perfectly located, just 0.3 miles from the most beautiful district in Paris, St Germain des Prés.
Perfect welcome and flawless room quality.
I recommend without any doubt !

Had a great weekend at the Aramis... perfect location, close walking distance from all the main Paris attractions and great value for money!
Friendly staff that gave me great advices to discover Paris! Would warmly recommend it to friends and family!

Haven’t been to Paris since I was a student staying in hostels. Was surprised how affordable this hotel is, given its great location, in a nice neighborhood, and the amenities. Wonderful open air market a few steps away. Short walk to Bon Marche for shopping. Bus stop and metro station out front (and another metro line a block away). Friendly staff.

Ok first off, the location is perfect . Abundance of shops and restaurants . There is even a mini grocery store nearby at the back street . If traveling as a couple, pls book a superior room because the standard room is super tiny . There is no way you can open your luggage because the space is just too tight to move . It’s a room for a single traveler with only a carry on. And this was on the 6th floor. The elevator only goes up to the 5th floor so you have to drag your luggage/s up the winding and narrow staircase . Bad enough the elevator is a size of a small refrigerator . It was so frustrating the night we arrived from the airport apart from being tired . Fortunately, the front desk staff were very understanding and patient with me since I was annoyed already. They were able to find us a superior room to our liking . So I commend them with excellent customer service.

Perfect central location opposite a Metro station. About a 15 minute walk to Notre Dame through safe and beautiful neighborhoods. Very close to the Luxembourg Gardens.
The room size was fine - it's central Paris so a little on the smaller side. Great to be able to open the windows fully. Room was very quiet - no traffic noise. Very clean. Very friendly and helpful staff.

Hotel is situated a couple of minutes walk from two different Metro lines - and is an easy walk from many of the sights and lots of wonderful restaurants (so we didn't eat in the hotel at all). Room was small but clean and lovely. Front desk staff were brilliant - especially Alessandro (I hope I have his name right!) who ordered us an airport shuttle bus. Only downside I found was that as I had booked thru a third party website I had to pay the tax when I checked out so I couldn't do express checkout - my own fault for not realising this, and it wasn't a big deal.

Folks at reception were extremely nice and helpful. Good central location. Parking was a bit expensive considering when we booked we thought it was included. Very nice room. Shopping, restraunts and convenience stores all close. No complaints.

This is the fourth time I’ve stayed at Aramis Saint-Germain in the last 15 years. The staff & service are great and the rooms clean. Excellent location; across the street from the metro. Lots of nearby restaurants and shops. Great soundproofing- quiet neighborhood at night. I only wish they hadn’t switched the breakfast to a “buffet” style. It used to be such a great breakfast experience.

My husband and I were as always impressed by the friendliness, of the staff of Aramis that were at all times available, and willing to help with a smile. The room was comfortable, very clean, and plesantly presented. We have stayed before in this hotel, and we will come back. Also, the fact that it is very centrally located makes life, even at the time of the strikes that we were there, easy enough to walk around.

We stayed here 3 nights for our Viking Paris to Normandy pre cruise . The location was excellent, Andy at the front desk was the best , I asked numerous questions and he provided me with maps and directions, he was like my personal concierge the whole time I stayed there. It is in an excellent location, the metro is across the street and you can travel around Paris from there , I highly recommend staying here !

We were there in Oct and had trouble with how warm our room was. This is the time when AC/to heat was occurring. He had to reset our heating so that we could have the fan blow. He knew exactly what the problem was and could resolve it.
Very helpful on directions and just making the stay a pleasant one.

Was a great price for a last minute buy(booked the night before), location was excellent easy less than 2 minute walk to the metro. Great food and shopping near by. The service was very helpful and staff was very friendly .

Slept well in comfortable bed, room was clean and quiet. The neighborhood was fun to explore and conveniently located near the Metro and bus lines. The staff were friendly and helpful. The breakfast was good.

The overall experience is quiet good.
Hotel location is excellent near the Metro and Bus Stations.
The surrounding are quiet at night busy at daytime.
Rooms are very small, but clean and tidy.
Price was very high, when I checked in, it's a high season in Paris at these dates

This was our 2nd stay at BW Aramis St-Germain. We were there in 2017 and the hotel has had some remodeling, adding a nice lobby, new key system while keeping the excellent service provided by very friendly, helpful staff. The location is perfect, with 2 Metro stations practically outside the door. The rooms are small as should be expected in this price range but they are clean and well maintained. We will definitely stay there whenever we are in Paris.

Perfect hotel - immaculately clean, everything in very good condition, very comfortable beds, good bathroom. Excellent breakfast. Exceptionally pleasant and helpful staff. Excellent location in smart area near Metro stations and good restaurants and shops. (Review from British couple, visited Paris several times before).

Could not have been better. The hotel layout and rooms are a little tight to say the least but easily made up for by efficient and friendly staff and the unsurpassed location. That is, in a square that comprises two great bistros (esp. L'Horizon), a coffee and pastry shop, a green grocers and most importantly Saint-Placide metro station. Easy walks to Gare Montparnasse and, in the opposite direction into Luxembourg Gardens and the 6th and 7th arrondissement. Quiet area but accessible to everywhere you want to go, by metro or foot. This will be a go-to for any future trips to Paris.

This small hotel is actually family owned and operated. That single fact makes this Best Western experience worth the high rating. It is a small hotel that feels more like a boutique than a chain. It is clean and well managed. The staff at the front desk all speak English (along with other languages) and Andy (owner / manager) may be the hardest working (and nicest) hotel Manager I have ever met. He was helpful with every request.

Expect small rooms and some without any view (though our upgraded room had two large windows opening to a quiet street). Both of our rooms had thermostats with strong AC, fast internet, and small, modern and very clean bathrooms. The Express breakfast with Coffee, fresh squeezed juice, and croissant at 6 Euro is a good deal considering a coffee alone is often 4 Euros in many shops.

A taxi to the middle of Paris' zone of tourism is about 15 minutes and 10 Euros (depending on traffic) though we walked (about 30 mins) most days. There are cafe's immediately outside the hotel as well as a bakery and small shop (with wine, food and drinks). In the opposite direction from the river (a 10 minute walk) is an amazing area with large crowds and outdoor restaurants that spilling into the streets from everywhere you look.

If you don't expect a Hilton in the heart of the Paris tourist district, you will enjoy this hotel.

Stayed with my son. Very clean, decent breakfast. No issues to have breakfast early 6am. Food was already laid out but staff not yet in. Front desk guy made me coffee as the breakfast lady did not arrive till 7am. Convenient to St. Germain area. Some great little restaurants in area La Georgette was excellent.

I love this hotel, staff very friendly & always smiling. Fast WIFI everywhere.
Rooms are large enough, beds are comfortable, room is isolated from any noise, have a balcony, A/C is good specially is July, bathroom size is fine.
Breakfast is good, but need some more varieties of cold cuts, as there's only one type.
Location is amazing, Metro Station Saint Placide is in front of the hotel, street full of shops like H&M, Micromania, Etam, Pandora, Fnac, Benetton, Zara, Levi's, Also C&A but at the end of street in Montparnasse shopping center, also many restaurants & cafes around the corner.
Overall we enjoyed our stay.

I was thrilled to find this hotel. It was a great price and had AC which was a must for me in July/August. I was pleasantly surprised to find a lovely hotel, clean rooms, very comfortable, and still very French. It’s in a great location but our room was completely quiet. The rooms are small but there was a ton of places to put our stuff. They use the space very well. And the staff couldn’t have been nicer or more helpful. I just can’t say enough about it. We had a great experience all around!

This is a great central hotel to enjoy your stay in Paris. Great bakery, cafe and bistro all downstairs. It is a family run business with the entire family being attentive and friendly and responsive to any needs you may have. Housekeeping was great and there is a breakfast available should you wish to pay a little extra for it. Overall, it truly exceeded my expectations. Do keep in mind the rooms are small in Paris no matter where you stay. Truth is, you shouldn't be spending too much time indoors :)

Clean, comfortable room and bed. Room is well insulated from outside sounds, making a good nights sleep possible. Outstanding front desk staff/manager who was very friendly, welcoming and able to readily answer questions both about the reservation and about the area. I was by myself so the room was appropriately sized. There is s very small elevator for those with luggage. The hotel has good Air conditioning and secure Wifi, which are both a must for me when I look at hotel bookings. Short walk to Luxembourg Garden, Galerie shopping and train/car rental at Gare Montparnasse.

Great location, neat and clean, great vibe, amazing balcony with super views - perfect to wake up with a pain au chocolat & coffee and watch the streets of Paris below. Only drawback is rooms a bit small, but hey, we’re in Paris and it’s all about the character! Extremely clean and tastefully renovated, would stay again.

I am a woman in her 50s traveling solo who had one night in Paris before going to Bordeaux. I took Le Bus from CDG and walked with easily with my suitcase to this hotel. The staff was very friendly! The room and hotel are clean. I felt safe. I got a good sleep. It's a great location to explore some of Paris. I plan on staying here again.

Been there this May for 5 nights.The Room was small like many parisian hotels. Bathroom was comfortable.breakfast we just had once, but was very good. The area is very close to a couple of metro stations,and there's a lot of cafes,patisiers,restaurants,a supermarket etc...it is also close to the Luxembourg gardens and Boulevard Saint Germain.
We highly recommend!

Room was neat and clean. The size of the room is small in comparison to American hotels, but typical of most European facilities. Staff was friendly and spoke in English when they realized that I spoke little French.

The location of Best Western Aramis Saint-Germain was excellent. We could walk to many venues and cabs and ubers were easily available when transportation was needed. The staff was knowledgeable and extremely helpful in answering questions. The accommodations were clean and comfortable. I would recommend this place to other travelers to Paris.

This was my third time of staying at the Aramis St. Germain, although only a short two day stay. The room was adequate and bathroom facilities were good. Staying on the 6th floor was difficult with luggage as the elevator only goes up to Floor Five. The desk personnel were wonderful and gave several recommendations for making our short time work....Thanks so much!

You walk out the entry and there are three restaurants/brasseries on the adjacent corners of Rue de Rennes. There is a bakery, chocolatier and newsstand within a block. Two different Metro lines are just steps away. This is a very busy street so the people-watching is a treat.

The hotel desk agents are personable, especially Alex who helped me immensely, and speak English well.

My fourth-floor "comfort" room features a double set of French casement windows that open up to a generous view of the vibrant street scene and of course admit a ton of beautiful French air and daylight. There is a functionally well-designed long counter for personal items, beverage glasses, etc. There also is a big closet and a well-appointed bathroom with good water pressure and shower/tub arrangement. The room has a fridge and safe too. Sleeping for me was decent all seven nights.

I will definitely book this hotel on my return to Paris as it is a tremendous value.

The location is great with easy Metro access and plenty of resturants, pastry shops and endless shopping availble. Easy walking distance to many attractions.It may not be a 4-5 star hotel by North American standards but was very acceptable for the 3 nights we stayed. Front desk staff were excellant. No issues encountered or regrets about having stayed at this hotel.

I stayed in Best Western Aramis Saint-Germain for 2 nights during my trip to Paris. The location of this hotel is great since there is a metro station in a few minutes and also you can walk to Luxembourgh Park in 15 minutes. Besides there are a lot of supermarkets and restaurants in a walking distance.

Very clean room decorated with internet and climate control system. My bed was comfortable, I didn't face any problems during my stay in this hotel.

The location could not be better - the Saint Placide metro station is right across the street and the Rennes metro station just a block away. Walkable to the Musée Orsay and Notre Dame. The front desk staff could not have been more helpful, and communicated with us in English with no problem. The only complaint would be the small elevator, but that is minor compared to the positive aspects of this location.

Perfect location for small shopping in Paris. Democratic price for stay cafees, restaurants, metro station and all main shops ar very close.
Rooms are small, but clean and nice. Breakfast is included, but there is plenty of nice breakfast places around. In front of hotel you can find chinese bistro with good food to take away.

We booked a family room for two nights in February half term. The room was very clean and the bathroom had lots of decent toiletries.

The Reception was being refurbished so it was temporarily re-located to the bar area, which was a shame because it meant the bar and breakfast area was out of use for guests. Breakfast was served in your room instead.

The Receptionist was extremely helpful on check-in and gave us some ideas of places to visit whilst we were in Paris.

The hotel has a good location with lots of restaurants close by.

I would definitely stay here again.

We spent 3 nights here and had breakfast in the hotel every morning. The lady on breakfast was very smiley :) and the breakfast room is nice and bright. The staff were all very friendly and helpful. There is a kettle and a minibar in the rooms. The bed was very comfortable. We had a quiet room on the Rue de Vaugirard side. There are lots of shops just outside - cafes and bakeries. The nearest metro stop is the Saint-Placide which is just outside the hotel. You can also pick up the RER B to/from the airport at the Luxembourg stop which is a very pleasant 15 minute walk via Rue de Fleurus through the gardens.

We loved the location on Rue de Rennes- not excessively touristy, close to several metro lines, short walk to Blvd St Germain - which has many excellent and reasonably priced restaurants, long but very doable walk to Isle de la Cite, les Halles, Place de la Concorde, Louvre (35 min walk) , shops and supermarkets close by, many Churches and museums nearby etc. St Placide metro is across the street and Rennes metro is a block away; Montparnasse RER (train direct from airport) and metro is 3 blocks away.

The hotel rooms are small but not by Parisian standards. Room was clean (though rug seemed a big questionable), bathroom was nice, small fridge where we could remove their drinks and put in ours, helpful staff at front desk, good recommendations on nearby restaurants. Elevator was quite small but functioned OK as did steep stairs. Room temperature was adjustable with thermostat. A fairly ample closet to put our stuff. Room has safe and TV including CNN in English, etc. We had the "comfort" room instead of "deluxe" but it was quite adequate. Apparently deluxe has an expresso machine instead of just a water boiler with (quite good) instant coffee and tea.

We liked the hotel would stay there again. Price was high (about $260 with breakfast for two) - two or three times what web sites advertised for this and other nearby hotels, but apparently some conventions in January raised the prices of this and other nearby hotels. Holiday Inn across the street was similar price - perhaps a tiny bit cheaper - but I would prefer this smaller hotel, all things considered.

Good instant coffee and tea in the hotel room. The breakfast was adequate (15 Euros if you pay or 6.5 for a petit dejeuner the latter avail 6 to 12). Full breakfast included hard boiled eggs, coffee or tea prepared for you, apple, sometimes banana, fruit cocktail, yogurt plain or flavored, cereals, croissants, bread, pain au chocolat - little rolled up pieces of ham. Not quite as nice as the full buffet choices at some hotels but quite adequate for our needs - full breakfast is only available 7 to 10:30.

Hotel is affiliated to Best Western, but not owned by them. We loved the area, liked the hotel and would stay there again if it is price competitive with holiday inn or other nearby hotels. Reception staff speaks English and French. Internet is free and worked well with my Samsung phone but for some reason didn't work with my wife's I phone - perhaps problem was her phone. Lots of places in Paris have free internet these days - restaurants, etc. We paid for a double (available at 2 PM) but we arrived at 9 AM - exhausted and they gave us a triple, available immediately at no extra charge.

First of all, a lot of mold and dust in the ventilation system (the photo is attached) which makes the room dangerous for health. I sneezed and coughed regularly, it stopped only with the opened window. Second, a very arrogant and never helpful person (actually the only one) at the reception - whatever I asked him the answer was "no". The last irritating thing - twice he couldn't print a bill without a mistake in my name. He told me that sent me it by email, but didn't do it. The location of the hotel is perfect & good cleaning.

My wife and I stayed in Hotel Aramis and everything was good. The front desk staff were very friendly and accommodating and we would stay there again. The location is close to shops, restaurant, bus stop and Metro.

Summary: I recommend this hotel for the combination of rating, price, and location.

Location: Saint-Germain is a desired location in Paris. You can do your own research on this. This particular Hotel has Bus Lines and two Major Metro lines (Metro 4) immediately outside the entrance and Metro 12 (two short blocks away). This is important to get around. There is a French restaurant (Le Trait d’Union) immediately next door on the corner. We ate their many times (breakfast, dinner, and late food and drinks). Excellent service with the pricing comparable to any French corner restaurant. We liked it because it is mainly a local “hang-out.” Other amenities that we used local to the hotel were a clean laundry mat (maps says 5 min walk) called Pressing Laverie at 5 Rue d’Alencon, the local grocery store (called Franpix), and no-frills coffee shop chain called Brioche Doree. Despite what other reviews say about the slow and bad services of waiters, in the eleven days, we did not experience any bad service at any of the many restaurants we visited. All waiters were polite and quick. We did not use any rating guides to pick where we ate. We ate when we got hungry, wherever we were.
Hotel amenities: Clean and up to date. Windows are practically sound proof. The hot water is instant. The down blanket was plenty to keep us warm. The heater worked perfectly. The elevator is very quiet. The employees are all 5 star. Very comfortable room for two people. We were on the 6th floor. The elevators only go to the 5th floor but worth the Great views. Taxi from CDG airport to the hotel was flat rate of $55 euros. I would definitely stay again.

We very much enjoyed our stay here. The rooms are small but comfortable and very clean. Great location we were able to walk to most of the tourist spots and there were lovely shops close by. And great food.

Staff exceptionally friendly and nice. Room always clean and has everything you may need: Coffee; mini-refrigerator; hair dryer; WiFi. Location excellent with many nearby cafes and restaurants. Next to the Metro.

This is a super hotel. The staff especially Alessandro are brilliant. The rooms are cozy and so quiet. The advice and recommendations are there on tap from Alex. Buses across the road will bring you almost everywhere and the metro is right beside the bus stop. It's a great location and the hotel has a really lovely feel to it. We will be back!

Great location updated bathroom clean rooms and bathroom which is very important for me the cleanliness Rooms on small size but overall experience great thank you hotel AramisLocation unbeatable on rue de Rennes Highly recommend

Convenient to Metro and buses. Lovely boulangerie across the street for quick retrieval of breakfast pastries. This was a guilty pleasure as a perfectly adequate breakfast was available through the hotel. The staff were all helpful, charming and friendly despite my mangled french. Our room was very quiet despite being on a busy road. The room was compact (small!) but the amenities were all there. I did not plan to dance in the room anyway.

All sights and cafés are within walking distance. 5 minute walk to Blvd Saint Germain with the famous cafés and 5 minutes in the opposite direction Tour Montparnasse and all the creperies. Very friendly and service minded hotel staff. A good place to stay.

Friendly staff. Clean nice rooms. Lobby was a bit small that even the luggages would struggle to fit. Good view of the Montparnasse from out window. Great location. Breakfast was not worth noting but everything else was good.

The Aramis is in a great location in a neighborhood with good restaurants and steps away from a metro station. Our room was clean and well appointed with a roomy bathroom and lots of hot water. It is small and family owned. The owners sometimes man the desk and are often seen carrying luggage and giving good information about getting around Paris. Breakfast is served in an interesting room facing the street so you can watch Parisians scurrying to work or school. Other breakfast options are only steps away.

Very convenient location with tube access on street and attractions. Rooms are bit smaller compared to US standards but include all amenities. breakfast buffet is good and Front desk staff are very professional.

Great Location..... a 20 minute walk from Notre Dame, The Louvre , Eiffel Tour , The Sienne. EASY to get to from the Airport using the RER and the Metro Line. Rooms are small but very comfortable and everything you need ..... They have Breakfast but I had to leave for the Airport really Early

Good hotel in great location. Price good compared with the boutique hotels close by.
Decent size room walk in shower' fridge' safe (free) wi fi all there.
Hotel reception excellent especially the American guy.

The gentlemen at the reception desk spoke perfect English. He was extremely helpful with directions and entertainment suggestions.( sept. 11-14) . Great variety of breakfast food. Walking distance to Galleries Lafayette, Montparnasse Tower and variety of restaurants .I recommend this hotel.

The staff were very friendly and most helpful. The hotel was clean and well maintained.
The rooms were quite small even for paris and had the bare minimums for a 3 star. There were no features or particular special touches to make the hotel at all interesting or memorable.

Our stay here was just wonderful. The staff is very helpful and accommodating. The location is so perfect - right next to Saint-Placide metro and easy access to anything you would like to see. I would highly recommend and I would definitely stay here again.

Close to metro stations which gave it a good location. The staff was very nice all the time and very helpful. I would definitely go to this hotel again. The rooms are clean and prepped everyday. Had no complaints.

This is just a really nice hotel located in central Paris with multiple nearby Metro stops so that you can get anywhere in Paris in less than 20-minutes. We were particularly impressed by the friendly, helpful, English-speaking staff. The rooms are typically sized for Paris, but value-priced. More importantly, rooms are bright, quiet, very clean & comfortable. We very much enjoyed this hotel and can highly recommend it.

For my family it was no doubt what hotel chain to choose for its high standards and comfort of the staying. It was our first travel to Paris and when planning the trip the above all and mandatory requirement was to have a triple room at a reasonable price in a walking distance or close to public transportation to get to the most must-see things in Paris. This hotel met our requirements to the full. A metro station just to cross the street (by the way, really convenient to get from and to CDG airport with just one change), bus lines leading to Paris attractions in the centre, as well as cafes, pastry shops and famous Montparnasse Blv restaurants – all so nearby, simply next door.
The triple room was comfortable, clean, neat and quiet, though the hotel stands at the cross roads, there was no street noise inside thanks to modern windows. Maybe some might say the room is rather small, but trust me, it is enough for three adults to relax after all-day-walks exploring the city and have good sleep in comfortable beds. The hotel provided all the necessary things: shelter, comfort and breakfast to start your day, not to forget tea/coffee machine in the room. I can’t but give many thanks to the hotel staff for their great hospitality. They kept our room tidy and clean, full of supplies, answered all our questions how to get here and there etc.; and special thanks to William for his great help providing us with some kind of administrative support. Should we have a chance to visit Paris again we would definitely stay at this hotel.
P.S. Other guests may have different opinion on the subject but the great impression of the hotel is reserved mine and only mine.

We stayed in Paris for couple of days for sightseeing. The hotel is in a great location. It is steps away from Metro line 4. It has plenty of shops and restaurants nearby and is within walking distance from Montparnasse, which has more eating and shopping options. The room is very clean and tastefully decorated. The hotel has AC, which we very much appreciated after spending long hot hours outdoor. The room is small, however, so need to be mindful of the room type when booking especially if you have luggage. The staff is very friendly, stored our luggage when we arrived too early. Would highly recommend this hotel.

First time visiting Paris on an extended stay... Hotel staff were very professional, personable and genuine. The location of the hotel is very close to public transportation and within walking distant to restaurants and other places of interest. Will surely re-book with them if in the area again!

Hotel was great. Room and bathroom where clean. The location was excellent. Just a few minutes to walk from important areas of Paris . Alessandro was great as well as an Italian staff member
Highly recommend

Had reserved and paid on arrival a Superior room. They first offered us a 1st Floor Comfort room, then found a Comfort room in 4th Floor. In my reservation I clearly asked for a room in a higher Floor. I do not write the wish to keep me warm!
It always spoils a little your welcome if you have to "discuss" the details on arrival.
I checked on the BW Aramis home page that we are paying for Superior room but the picture of Comfort shows our room exactly. They denied any refund on reception. So please check the prices and what it includes when you reserve.
The standard ot cleaning was good, but no replacement for shampoos and shower gels without asking. The hairdryer was from the sixties and did not work properly.
The location of the hotel was excellent. Shops, restarants, bus routes, metro very close. But the earlier TA comments on which I decided the hotel were not valid.

We have stayed at this hotel several times now and every time the experience is great. The staff is always pleasant, the rooms are quiet and comfortable and the location could not be better. I love having a home away from home in Paris!
